(25000, 'Plemazol 0.1% oral drops 20 ml(n/a)', 'بليمازول 0.1% نقط للفم 20مل', '', '4', 'Metoclopramide', 'Cid', 'Drops', 'نقط', '', 'Antiemetic', '0.1%', 'Metoclopramide in the oral tablet form is used for symptomatic treatment of both acute and recurrent diabetic gastroparesis, in addition to the treatment of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD) in patients who have failed to respond to traditional therapy.[L8414] A nasal spray formulation is also indicated to treat adults with acute, recurrent diabetic gastroparesis.[L14381]
